1041:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c **** /**
1042:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * @ingroup tcp_raw
1043:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * Connects to another host. The function given as the "connected"
1044:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * argument will be called when the connection has been established.
1045:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  *  Sets up the pcb to connect to the remote host and sends the
1046:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * initial SYN segment which opens the connection.
1047:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  *
1048:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * The tcp_connect() function returns immediately; it does not wait for
1049:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * the connection to be properly setup. Instead, it will call the
1050:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * function specified as the fourth argument (the "connected" argument)
1051:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * when the connection is established. If the connection could not be
1052:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * properly established, either because the other host refused the
1053:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * connection or because the other host didn't answer, the "err"
1054:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * callback function of this pcb (registered with tcp_err, see below)
1055:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * will be called.
1056:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  *
1057:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * The tcp_connect() function can return ERR_MEM if no memory is
1058:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * available for enqueueing the SYN segment. If the SYN indeed was
1059:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * enqueued successfully, the tcp_connect() function returns ERR_OK.
1060:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  *
1061:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * @param pcb the tcp_pcb used to establish the connection
1062:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * @param ipaddr the remote ip address to connect to
1063:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * @param port the remote tcp port to connect to
1064:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * @param connected callback function to call when connected (on error,
1065:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****                     the err callback will be called)
1066:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * @return ERR_VAL if invalid arguments are given
1067:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  *         ERR_OK if connect request has been sent
1068:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  *         other err_t values if connect request couldn't be sent
1069:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  */
