2097:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c **** /**
2098:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * @ingroup tcp_raw
2099:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * Specifies the polling interval and the callback function that should
2100:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * be called to poll the application. The interval is specified in
2101:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * number of TCP coarse grained timer shots, which typically occurs
2102:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * twice a second. An interval of 10 means that the application would
2103:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * be polled every 5 seconds.
2104:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  *
2105:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * When a connection is idle (i.e., no data is either transmitted or
2106:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * received), lwIP will repeatedly poll the application by calling a
2107:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * specified callback function. This can be used either as a watchdog
2108:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * timer for killing connections that have stayed idle for too long, or
2109:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * as a method of waiting for memory to become available. For instance,
2110:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * if a call to tcp_write() has failed because memory wasn't available,
2111:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * the application may use the polling functionality to call tcp_write()
2112:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  * again when the connection has been idle for a while.
2113:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp.c ****  */
